<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,457,1837,1863]" box="[189,457,1837,1863]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,1837,1863]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,1837,1863]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,1886,2025]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
In addition to the characters in the key, 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[668,1100,1886,1912]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albolobata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[668,1100,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) albolobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1110,1202,1886,1912]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[280,433,1924,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="licina" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis box="[280,433,1924,1951]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. (A.) licina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[443,536,1924,1950]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the ventral lobe of both gonostyli narrower, apicodorsal part of the right superior lobe shorter and by having the ventral part of the left superior lobe with more prominent anterior, medial and posterior lobes (
<figureCitation box="[748,817,1999,2025]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[195,1394,992,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[189,1399,982,1897]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 7. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) albolobata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Posterior part of sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830553/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
<potCollectionCode box="[817,877,1999,2025]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">B–D</potCollectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,324,265,291]" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[189,1398,312,373]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[681,808,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albolobata">
<emphasis box="[681,808,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">albolobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘white-lobed’, referring to the white subtriangular lobe posteriorly on male sternum 
<potCollectionCode box="[746,777,347,373]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">IV</potCollectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
